HEADWORD: Subtectacle
<hw>Sub*tec"ta*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>sub-</ets> + L. <ets>tectum</ets> a roof.]</ety> <def>A space under
a roof; a tabernacle; a dwelling.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
